Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "krajnje" in different forms and positions:

1. Krajnje je vreme da počnemo da razmišljamo o letovanju. (*krajnje* vreme = high time; It's high time we start thinking about the summer vacation.)
2. Spremni smo da učinimo sve što je krajnje potrebno da rešimo ovaj problem. (*krajnje* potrebno = absolutely necessary; We're ready to do everything that's absolutely necessary to solve this problem.)
3. Ovaj koncert je krajnje dosadan. (krajnje = extremely; This concert is extremely boring.)
4. Krajnje je vreme da se odlučiš šta želiš da radiš u životu. (*krajnje* vreme = high time; It's high time you decide what you want to do in life.)
5. Ova situacija je krajnje neprijatna. (*krajnje* neprijatna = extremely unpleasant; This situation is extremely unpleasant.)
6. Krajnje je važno da budemo oprezni u ovakvim situacijama. (*krajnje* važno = extremely important; It's extremely important that we are careful in situations like this.)
7. Znam da je krajnje nezgodno, ali moram da vas pitam da mi pozajmite novac. (*krajnje* nezgodno = extremely inconvenient; I know it's extremely inconvenient, but I have to ask you to lend me some money.)
8. Krajnje je vreme da se okrenemo budućnosti. (*krajnje* vreme = high time; It's high time we turn to the future.)

I hope this helps! Let me know if you have any other questions.